Class CompositionEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.BaseEntry

    PrototypeEntry

    public class CompositionEntry
extends MultiPropertyEntry
    Stores several properties about a compound and its composition. Can store information regarding multiple properties of the material represented by the composition.

      • CompositionEntry

        public CompositionEntry(java.lang.String Composition)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Make a new instance by parsing the composition of an object, provided by a string.

        First splits using the regex [A-Z][^A-Z] to separate each component of the alloy. This assumes that capitalization is used property. Then, splits each component into the Alphabetical part (assumed to be the element name) and the numeric part (amount of element). If no numeric part is present, 1 is assumed. An element can be appear more than once.

        Parameters:
        Composition - Composition of entry
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If parse fails

      • rectifyEntry

        public final void rectifyEntry(boolean toSort)
        Makes sure this entry is in a proper format. Must be run from constructor

        Performs the following operations:

        • Optional: Ensure Element and Fraction are sorted according to the order listed in SortingOrder.
        • Ensure that the sum of Fraction is equal to 1.
        • Set NumberInCell is equal to the original sum of Fraction.
        Parameters:
        toSort - Whether to sort elements in "Sorting order"
